<br>
Gulf of Gunthak: All green to me in the cave to Luggards area, all greens agro that I've run into. Other than undead, haven't found anything that sees through invis.<br>
Lugards all seem to be casters, ench and wiz. Lt blue to 55. Random loot drops are sweet. Got a nice ring last night, and the day before both Walli and Moko got a nice shoulder item (or was it a head slot?) <br>
Citizens in Luggard area were green-lt blue. No special drops yet from them.<br>
Dropped weapons seem to sell for FS prices.<br>
<br>
<br>
Dulak's Harbor: Green - drk blue here. Levi doesn't work here. Didn't run into any mobs here that saw through invis. AGRO IS HUGE !!! but if your careful it can be controlled. I was fine till I got agro through some walls. Mobs are well disperesed and spawn rates are decent (6-10min). Wandering guards/guardians seem to be higher than many of the static mobs that I've seen so far. <br>
Gem/jewlery drops seem to be random here, about the same as sea furies in OoT, with some higher gems thrown in, a Diamond dropped somewhere in there the 1st night. Weaps here also seem to sell at FS prices, there are some stat weaps that drop, may be able to be sold in bazaar as newbie weaps.<br>
<br>
Torgiran Mines: Didn't spend much time in here. Get here through Dulak's Harbor. Mobs seem to be very spread out. Walli, Moko, Solaric, and Ehron stayed after I left, they may have more info here. Mobs I saw were all dk blue to 55.<br>
<br>
Crypt of Nadox: Lava...Lava..Lava...Oh..and Lots of Lava. I couldn't exploere here to well. Levi doesn't work here. Elementals here that I saw were dk blue to 55, and see through invis I think, can't remeber. Also from listening to Moko there might be two entrances to this zone from Gunthak. He was talking about a temple and zoning in to here (I think, could be confused) and where I zoned in there was no temple.<br>
<br>
Hate's Fury: Haven't found this zone, looks to be off of Crypt of Nadox.<br>
<br>
Over all the zones seem to be well done, that I have visited. What loot that has dropped is seems to be very good, though not all that common.<br>
<br>
